From: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
Date:   Thu Mar 12 14:29:23 2026 +0200
Subject: objtool: Fix false-positives
Patch-mainline: Never, our own fix
References: git-fixes

That -flive-patching compiler option introduces the following false positives in objtools:

    vmlinux.o: warning: objtool: hv_crash_nmi_local+0x40: crash_nmi_callback() is missing a __noreturn annotation
    vmlinux.o: warning: objtool: fred_sysvec_reboot+0x2d: __sysvec_reboot() is missing a __noreturn annotation
    vmlinux.o: warning: objtool: ghes_notify_nmi+0x268: __ghes_panic() is missing a __noreturn annotation
    vmlinux.o: warning: objtool: sysvec_reboot+0x38: __sysvec_reboot() is missing a __noreturn annotation

In order to keep the build objtool clean fix them by annotating __ghes_panic as __noreturn
and excluding the others from being checked for noreturn. This prevents objtool
warnings being treated as false positives.

Signed-off-by: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
[mbenes:
  Add more noreturn annotations and false positives to the list.
  SL-16.1 kernel build is now clean of objtool warnings.
  Also fix indentation and refresh the patch.
]
Signed-off-by: Miroslav Benes <mbenes@suse.cz>
